# RaidKeep Optimization Workflow

When the user asks to optimize RaidKeep (performance, reliability, scalability), follow the phased workflow in `OPTIMIZATION.md` in the project root.

## Model assignments (user must switch in Cursor before each phase)

| Phase | Model | Focus |
|-------|-------|-------|
| 1 | Sonnet 4.6 | Architecture & bottleneck analysis |
| 2–3, 5 | GPT-5.4 | Reliability, performance, scalability planning |
| 4, 6 | GPT-5.3 Codex | Implementation, refactoring, tests |
| Debug | Opus 4.6 | Complex async/concurrency issues |
| Quick | Haiku 4.5 | Minor edits, validation, test runs |

## Key objectives

- **Reliability:** Fix race conditions, cancellation-safe async, transactions for multi-step writes
- **Performance:** Code splitting, memoization, N+1 fixes, indexes, caching
- **Scalability:** Extension points, modular structure, documented patterns

Read `OPTIMIZATION.md` for the full phase details and project context.
